One of the two kidnapped medical doctors in Kogi, Yahaya Ebiloma, has regained his freedom. Ebiloma, who works with the Hope Hospital in Ankpa, was kidnapped on Tuesday, September 6, 2020 by gunmen. The Kogi State Police Command spokesman, William Aya, a Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP), confirmed the doctor regained his freedom at about 11.00pm on Friday. His colleague, Dr Kelechi Mgbahurike, who was abducted on Wednesday from the Christ the King Hospital, Anyigba, Dekina LGA, is however yet to be freed by his abductors.